<div class="header"><h1>Chemical Name for Protein-Bound Glutamate</h1></div>
<div class="body">

<p>Proteins are large biomolecules that are made up of smaller units called amino
acids. There are 20 different amino acids that can be used to build proteins, and
each amino acid has a unique chemical structure <sup><a href="#src-amino-1">1</a>.</sup></p>

<p>Glutamate is one of the 20 amino acids that can be found in proteins. When it is part
of a protein, it is known as a protein-bound glutamate.</p>

<p>The chemical name for protein-bound glutamate is "L-glutamate." The "L" in the name
refers to the fact that the amino acid is in the L-configuration, which is one of two possible
configurations that an amino acid can adopt. The other configuration is called the
D-configuration <sup><a href="#src-amino-2">2</a>.</sup></p>

<p>Protein-bound glutamate can be found in many different proteins in the body, including
enzymes, hormones, and structural proteins. It is an important component of protein and
plays a key role in many functions within the body.</p>

